<HL>
   Sanwa Will Merge Two Units
</HL>
<DATE>
07/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10
</SO>
<CO>
   J.SWB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Sanwa Bank Ltd. announced that it obtained Bank
of England approval to merge its British subsidiary, Sanwa
International Ltd., with the Associated Japanese Bank
International Ltd., which became a Sanwa unit March 30.
   The merger, to be completed in August, will be called
Sanwa International PLC.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Japanese Bank International was launched in
London in 1970 by Sanwa, the Nomura Securities Co., Dai Ichi
Kangyo Bank Ltd. and Mitsui Bank Ltd.
   In addition to the current businesses of the two banks,
which include the underwriting and sale of bonds, the merger
will also offer general banking services.
   Sanwa, a leading Japanese city bank, also has offices in
Switzerland and West Germany.
</TEXT>
