<HL>
   France's Industrial Production
</HL>
<DATE>
07/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   PARIS -- France's industrial production index rose a
seasonally adjusted 0.3% in May from April and 1.5% from a
year earlier, according to preliminary figures of the
National Statistics Institute.
   The 0.3% rise represents a slowdown from April's
exceptionally high growth rate of 1.4%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A breakdown showed that the May advance was spread over
most sectors of the economy except energy.
   Automobiles and other consumer durable goods led the way,
with a rise of 4.8% from April and 1.6% from a year earlier.
   The May index stood at 112.5, up from April's revised
112.2 and the year-earlier level of 110.8. The index covers
output in all sectors of the economy except building and is
based on 1985 equaling 100.
</TEXT>
