<HL>
   Pier 1's June Sales Up
</HL>
<DATE>
07/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   PIR
</CO>
<LP>
   FORT WORTH, Texas -- Pier 1 Imports said that sales rose
almost 12% in June but that sales for those at stores open
more than a year fell 2.6%.
   The company attributed the slip in sales at older stores
to a decline in furniture sales. "The consumer has lost a
little confidence in the economy and is buying less
furniture," said Robert G. Herndon, chief financial officer
for the home-furnishing retailer. Mr. Herndon said the
company's sales of soft goods remain strong.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In June, Pier 1 had sales of $56.9 million, up from $50.9
million a year ago.
