WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   G.DAI LABOR
</CO>
<LP>
   Mercedes-Benz AG said the company's workers' council
agreed to special Saturday overtime shifts to help the
company cope with rising demand.
   The auto-making arm of Daimler-Benz AG said that special
shifts will be added on "several Saturdays" beginning
September. The overtime shifts will affect the company's
plants in Stuttgart-Untertuerkheim, Sindelfingen and Bremen.
